torique, puis les thèmes du réductionnisme, de la complexité, des méthodes expérimentales. Il aborde ensuite les théories évolutionnistes et conclut sur l'interdisciplinarité. Un appel à l'interaction sciences-société termine le livre.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn French.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 25. Feb 2021) 4aLife sciences/Biology. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology.2bisacsh1 aBornarel, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDebru, Claude, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacrot, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMache, Régis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPebay-Peyroula, Eva, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9782759801367423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9782759801367.jpg  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK